Creating an HR analytics dashboard in Power BI can provide valuable insights into your organization's workforce. Here are some key components you might include:

Employee Overview: Metrics like total employee count, active employees, and employee demographics (age, gender, education).

Attrition Analysis: Charts showing attrition rates, reasons for leaving, and attrition by department or job role.

Job Satisfaction: Visualizations of employee feedback on job satisfaction, work-life balance, and engagement levels.

Performance Metrics: Data on employee performance, promotions, and training participation.

Salary Analysis: Insights into salary distributions, pay equity, and comparisons by department or role.


